3. Business Logic Layer
Class Diagram

The Business Logic Layer is composed of several core entities that represent the main components of the HBnB system. These entities are defined in the Class Diagram, which shows their attributes, methods, and relationships.

The main entities in the system are:

User
Place
Review
Amenity
BaseModel

User

The User entity represents individuals who interact with the platform.

Attributes include:

first_name

last_name

email

password

places

reviews

Users can create places and write reviews about places.

Place

The Place entity represents a property listed on the platform.

Attributes include:

title

description

id

price

owner

address

max_guests

reviews

Each place belongs to a user and can receive multiple reviews.

Review

The Review entity represents feedback written by a user about a place.

Attributes include:

id

reviewer

place

rating

comment

author

Each review is associated with a specific place and a specific user.

Amenity

The Amenity entity represents additional features that can be associated with places.

Attributes include:

id

name

description

created_at

updated_at

Amenities allow places to describe available services such as WiFi, parking, or air conditioning.

BaseModel

The BaseModel entity provides common attributes shared across multiple entities.

Attributes include:

id

created_at

updated_at

Methods include:

save()

to_dict()

This base class ensures consistency across entities and simplifies data management.

